**Overall Meaning:**

This verse emphasizes the importance of introspection and self-realization over external pursuits. It advises abandoning the pursuit of worldly desires, the limitations of the physical body, and even the adherence to external scriptures. Instead, one should focus on self-study and contemplation to discover the true nature of the Self.

**Translation:**

**Giving up following the world, giving up following the body, giving up following the scriptures, engage in self-study and reflection.**
